pageDescription: Time actions make working with time across devices easy.

comment.shortText:
Gets the shared time that has been agreed upon between devices in the inst as the number of miliseconds since midnight January 1st, 1970 UTC-0 (i.e. the Unix Epoch).
This is what your device's clock thinks the inst clock says.
comment.text: If an agreed upon time cannot be determined (for example, because collaboration is disabled in the inst), then this value will always be `NaN`.

tags.text:
Toast the current shared time
os.toast(os.agreedUponTime);

comment.shortText:
Gets the shared time that has been agreed upon between devices but with an additional 50ms offset added.
This offset attempts to ensure that changes/events will be recieved by all connected devices by the time it occurs, thereby making synchronized actions easier to perform.
comment.text: If an agreed upon time cannot be determined (for example, because collaboration is disabled in the inst), then this value will always be `NaN`.

comment.shortText: Gets the average latency between this device's clock and the inst clock in miliseconds. Lower values tend to indicate a good connection while higher values tend to indicate a bad connection.
comment.text: If an agreed upon time cannot be determined (for example, because collaboration is disabled in the inst), then this value will always be `NaN`.

comment.shortText: Gets the average latency between this device's clock and the inst clock in miliseconds. Lower values tend to indicate a good connection while higher values tend to indicate a bad connection.
comment.text: If an agreed upon time cannot be determined (for example, because collaboration is disabled in the inst), then this value will always be `NaN`.

comment.shortText: Gets the calculated time offset between the inst clock and the local clock. This value is equivalent to `os.agreedUponTime - os.localTime`.
comment.text: If an agreed upon time cannot be determined (for example, because collaboration is disabled in the inst), then this value will always be `NaN`.

comment.shortText: Gets the calculated time offset between the inst clock and the local clock. This value is equivalent to `os.agreedUponTime - os.localTime`.
comment.text: If an agreed upon time cannot be determined (for example, because collaboration is disabled in the inst), then this value will always be `NaN`.

comment.shortText: Gets the spread between calculated time offsets. Higher values indicate that [`os.agreedUponTime`](ref:os.agreedUponTime) is less accurate. Lower values indicate that [`os.agreedUponTime`](ref:os.agreedUponTime) is more accurate.
comment.text: If an agreed upon time cannot be determined (for example, because collaboration is disabled in the inst), then this value will always be `NaN`.

comment.shortText: Gets the spread between calculated time offsets. Higher values indicate that {@link os.agreedUponTime} is less accurate. Lower values indicate that {@link os.agreedUponTime} is more accurate.
comment.text: If an agreed upon time cannot be determined (for example, because collaboration is disabled in the inst), then this value will always be `NaN`.
